# gatOS /etc/os-release template — edit this file, then rebuild the guest image.
#
# build-image.sh fills the @PLACEHOLDERS@ and expands the @BANNER@ / @TAGLINE@
# markers with the colour art from gatos-banner / gatos-tagline, writing the
# result to the guest's /etc/os-release.
#
#   @VERSION_ID@  guest image version (guest/GUEST_VERSION)
#   @ALPINE@      Alpine release the image was built from (e.g. 3.24.0)
#   @VERSION@     a combined "<guest> (Alpine <alpine>)" string
#
# The standard KEY=value fields below stay machine-readable; the banner/tagline
# and the free-form lines underneath are purely cosmetic (this file is shown by
# `cat /etc/os-release`, not sourced by anything in the guest).
NAME="gatOS"
ID=gatos
ID_LIKE=alpine
VERSION="@VERSION@"
VERSION_ID=@VERSION_ID@
PRETTY_NAME="gatOS @VERSION_ID@ - a Kitten Space Agency OS, based on Alpine Linux @ALPINE@"
HOME_URL="https://github.com/meow-sci/gatOS"
SUPPORT_URL="https://github.com/meow-sci/gatOS"
BUG_REPORT_URL="https://github.com/meow-sci/gatOS/issues"
LOGO=gatos

@BANNER@

@TAGLINE@

A real, minimal Alpine Linux running inside a QEMU microVM.
Vehicle telemetry mounts at /sim when the game provides it.
